Gödel’s Mathematical Work
2. Gödel’s Mathematical Work

Below is an examination of some of Gödel’s main
contributions in logic and set theory. This treatment of
Gödel’s technical work is not exhaustive, omitting
discussion of Gödel’s work in physics and his work on the
decision problem. These will be treated in the sequel to this
entry.

For a complete chronology of Gödel’s work the reader is
referred to that compiled by John Dawson in volume I of
Gödel’s Collected Works (Gödel 1986, p. 37).
